 Conclusion and Future Work  
- Machine learning models successfully predict calories burnt with high accuracy.  
- Random Forest and XGBoost models outperformed other algorithms.  
- Linear Regression provided a baseline and tended to underfit.  
- SVR performs well for smaller datasets; KNN is effective but slower on large datasets.  
- Future work includes deploying the model as a standalone app or web interface, integrating real-time data from wearable devices, and exploring deep learning approaches for enhanced accuracy.

